Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @green bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Transfer @nutritional yeast{1/2%tsp} to a #small bowl{}; set aside for serving. (You'll use the rest of the nutritional yeast in Step 3.)

== Veggies ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} (large #pot{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, mushrooms, and zucchini; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> While veggies cook, move on to Step 3!

In the last minute of cooking, add tomatoes and garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @water{2%tbsp} and cook, stirring constantly, until liquid has mostly reduced, about ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

== Polenta ==

While veggies cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @precooked polenta{1}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/3%cup}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add remaining @nutritional yeast{3/2%tbsp} and cook, stirring, until thickened and warmed through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> If polenta seems too thick, add water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches desired consistency.

== To Serve ==

Divide polenta between shallow #bowls{}. Top with sautéed veggies. Sprinkle with reserved nutritional yeast and scallion greens. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.